\subtree{
\title{Substrate recoloring : be в†¦ b3e, proven in Rust}
\p{B3 is an operad morphism #{F} recolouring the front of the pipeline (Byteв†¦Trit, Lineв†¦Line3,
Parseв†¦Parse3) and fixing #{\{\mathtt{Cell},\mathtt{Atlas},\mathtt{Frame}\}}. The kernel TTY is
byte-law (termios CSIZE = bits CS5..CS8), so B3 is a userspace parser swap (or a new N-TRIT line
discipline). Two parsers вЂ” byte+ESC-sentinel vs sign-trit-no-sentinel вЂ” drive the SAME Perform
handler and produce the IDENTICAL screen. The screen is the alibi; the assertion passes:}
\pre{\startverb
  b3e (sign-trit, no ESC):  screen="ABCEIH"  ctrl=[newline, tab, csi:7]
  be  (byte, ESC sentinel): screen="ABCEIH"  ctrl=[newline, tab, csi:7]
    same screen (squint boundary)? true   в†ђ b3e вЉ‘ be : the screen is the alibi
    same control-plane (interior)? true
  вњ“ Perform/Handler invariant across the parser swap.  (rustc -O b3e.rs ; assert passed)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Grounding (real category-theory of consciousness)}
\ul{
\li{Tsuchiya & Saigo вЂ” Yoneda for consciousness: qualia = relations; Q-arrows are \em{nearly indistinguishable} (= the squint).}
\li{A Compositional Model of Consciousness (Entropy 2021) вЂ” symmetric monoidal / process theory (= the operad).}
\li{Category theory in consciousness science (Synthese 2024) вЂ” mathematizing phenomenology.}
}
\p{This construction re-derived these independently: Fix(F) = Yoneda-invariant content, the squint =
the nearly-indistinguishable arrows, the colored operad = the SMC compositional model. CIMC =
the colored cells whose conserved symmetry is the valence.}
